@jonatack it might be useful to expand the `debug.log` section in developer notes with some guidance. E.g. it seems good practice to always use `LogPrintfCategory`, always pick a category and then use `>= BCLog::Level::Warning` for things you always want in the logs even when the user did not pick the specific `-debug` setting.

@ajtowns I think `BCLog::Level:None` is off-limits, from the description of f1379aeca9d3a8c4d3528de4d0af8298cb42fee4: "replace the unused BCLog::Level:None string "none" with an empty string as the case will never be hit"

That said, `warning` feels inappropriate* since this message is rarely bad news. Maybe we need a new level above `Info`, like `GlobalInfo`?

`* =` but not a big enough deal to make this PR needlessly complicated, using `warning` for now seems fine, since we don't actually print the word "warning" in the log.

